<static> EarthServerGenericClient.combinedCallBack(callback, numberToCombine)
Small helper to synchronise multiple request callbacks. After all callbacks to this helper are received the ResponseData object with all response data is send to the module. After each request is received a progress update is send to the module.
Defined in: ServerRequest.js.
Parameters:
callback
- Module which requests the data.
numberToCombine
- Number of callbacks that shall be received.

<static> EarthServerGenericClient.getWCPSImage(callback, responseData, url, query, DemInAlpha)
Starts a WCPS query and stores the received image in the responseData. If a dem is encoded in the alpha channel it will be extracted and also stored. Set DemInAlpha Flag in this case.
Defined in: ServerRequest.js.
Parameters:
callback
- Object to do the callback.
responseData
- Instance of the ServerResponseData.
url
- URL of the WCPS service.
query
- The WCPS query.
DemInAlpha
- Flag if a dem is encoded in the alpha channel.

Returns:
true if mobile platform, false if not
<static> EarthServerGenericClient.progressiveWCPSImageLoader(callback, WCPSurl, WCPSqueries, DemInAlpha)
The progressive WCPS loader initiate multiple queries consecutively. As soon as one response is received the next query is executed. Every response is given to the given callback. Note: The WCPS loader starts with the last query in the array (LIFO).
Defined in: ServerRequest.js.
Parameters:
callback
- Module that requests the WCPS images.
WCPSurl
- URL of the WCPS service.
WCPSqueries
- Array of WCPS queries. (LIFO)
DemInAlpha
- Flag if a dem is encoded in the alpha channel.
